  "story": {
    "intro": [
      "The beacon of Emberwick has gone cold, and the night fleet is sailing blind toward the rocks.",
      "You are Wick, a lantern spirit no taller than a teacup, with one stubborn flame and a long way up.",
      "Climb the great clockwork lighthouse. Relight the lamp before the tide turns."
    ],
    "levelIntros": [
      "The Quay Steps: fog on the water, cranes creaking overhead. Start climbing, little light.",
      "The Gearworks: the lighthouse's heart still turns. Mind the steam, ride the gears, keep your flame lit.",
      "The Lamp Gallery: wind howls through broken glass. The beacon is close. So is its keeper."
    ],
    "bossIntro": "The Rust Warden clanks out of the dark. It was built to guard the lamp - it just forgot who from.",
    "victory": [
      "The lamp blazes! Far below, the night fleet cheers as the harbor lights answer one by one.",
      "Wick curls up inside the warm glass. Some spirits are small. Their light is not."
    ],
    "defeat": [
      "Your flame gutters out on the cold stairs. The lighthouse waits, patient as stone.",
      "Take a breath, little light. Every climb starts again at the bottom step."
    ]
  },
